			<table  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="white">
				<tr>
					<td colspan="2" class="Table_head"><a name="top"></a>
						<font size="4px"><b>GUIDELINES ON MANAGING MY FORUM</b></font><br>					</td>
				<tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text"><font size="4px" class="Table_Sub_head"><b>For Division Administrators and Moderators</b></font></td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text">&nbsp;</td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td class="body_detail_text"><font size="4px" class="Table_Sub_Topic"><u><i>Our Approach to User Confidentiality </i></u></font></td>
			      <td  align="right" nowrap="nowrap">
							<a href="#top"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_up.gif' border="0" alt="Back"></a> <a href="#bottom"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_down.gif' border="0"></a></td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text"><ol>
				    <br>
                    <li>We respect the need for confidentiality in providing genuine and sincere views and comments. </li>
				    <li>To encourage free-flowing dialogue within the Discussion Forum, users&rsquo; personal information, other than the hobbies and their personalised nicknames, will not be available to Moderators or any other users.</li>
				    <li>As respondents in surveys and consultation papers need to be contactable, only statutory names, not nicknames, will be reflected in survey and consultation paper responses. </li>
				    <li>Identities are only known to the Main Administrators of My Forum, who are staff of MOE Corporate Communications Division. We will NOT share identities with other users, except where follow-up action is needed for users who contravene the Terms of Use.</li>
				    </ol>				  </td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text">&nbsp;</td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td class="body_detail_text"><font size="4px" class="Table_Sub_Topic"><u><i>Official Secrets Act</i></u></font></td>
			      <td  align="right" nowrap="nowrap">
							<a href="#top"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_up.gif' border="0" alt="Back"></a> <a href="#bottom"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_down.gif' border="0"></a></td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text"><ol>
				    <br>
                    <li>All My Forum users are bound by the Official Secrets Act (OSA). Any unauthorised dissemination of information, such as divulging sensitive and confidential information to other stakeholders, internal or external eg the media, is an offence under the OSA. </li>
				    <li>To make this clear to all, please include in all documents to be posted on My Forum the header &ldquo;RESTRICTED: FOR INTERNAL CIRCULATION ONLY&rdquo;. </li>
				    </ol>				  </td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text">&nbsp;</td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td class="body_detail_text"><font size="4px" class="Table_Sub_Topic"><u><i>Moderating the Discussion Forum</i></u></font></td>
			      <td  align="right" nowrap="nowrap">
							<a href="#top"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_up.gif' border="0" alt="Back"></a> <a href="#bottom"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_down.gif' border="0"></a></td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text"><ol>
				                     <br>
                    <li>The My Forum Discussion Forum is a platform where MOE staff can exchange views freely on policy or work related issues. For greater diversity of views, we would encourage Moderators to be inclusive and not moderate views unnecessarily. </li>
				    <li>However, the Moderator has the right to remove postings that are:
				      <ol>
                          <b>-</b> Defamatory
			          </ol>
				      <ol>
                          <b>-</b> Name-calling
			          </ol>
				      <ol>
                          <b>-</b> Obscene
			          </ol>
				      <ol>
                          <b>-</b> Vulgar
			          </ol>
				      <ol>
                          <b>-</b> Sexually oriented
			          </ol>
				      <ol>
                          <b>-</b> Hateful
			          </ol>
				      <ol>
                          <b>-</b> Threatening
			          </ol>
				      <ol>
                          <b>-</b> Baseless personal accusations
			          </ol>
				      <ol>
                          <b>-</b> Or any such materials not tolerated on the forum
			          </ol>
			        </li>
				    <li>The Moderator also reserves the right to remove postings that are unrelated to the topics, including promotion or direct selling advertisements</li>
				    <li>For posts that may require an official response from a Division, Moderators should highlight the postings to their Division Administrator who would assess and initiate the crafting of a reply, if necessary. Replies will be posted by the Moderator on My Forum, under the official nickname &ldquo;HQ&rdquo;. All such replies will be highlighted on the front-page of the Discussion Forum module. </li>
				    <li>Posts that generally contain the following should be highlighted for assessment and consideration for reply by Divisions:
			        <li>Misinformation perpetuated by other users</li>
				    <li>Misunderstanding of policies which led to wrong conclusions perpetuated by subsequent posts</li>
				    <li>Questions posed directly to Divisions by user/s</li>
				    </ol>				  </td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text">&nbsp;</td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td class="body_detail_text"><font size="4px" class="Table_Sub_Topic"><u><i>Selecting Discussion Threads, Consultation Papers and Surveys for &ldquo;Private&rdquo; Participation</i></u></font></td>
			      <td  align="right" nowrap="nowrap">
							<a href="#top"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_up.gif' border="0" alt="Back"></a> <a href="#bottom"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_down.gif' border="0"></a></td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text"><br>
                    <ol>
                      <li>Discussion threads, consultation papers and surveys can either be &ldquo;public&rdquo; or &ldquo;private&rdquo;. All My Forum users can access and respond in &ldquo;public&rdquo; discussion threads, consultation papers and surveys, whereas only invited participants will view and respond in &ldquo;private&rdquo; consultation papers and surveys. </li>
                      <li>We appreciate Divisions&rsquo; need for specific and potentially sensitive discussion topics, surveys and consultation papers to be kept &ldquo;private&rdquo;. CCD leaves the selection of &ldquo;private&rdquo; consultation  paper exercises &ndash; be it in the form of discussion threads, surveys, or consultation papers &ndash; to the discretion of Divisions. However, we strongly encourage Divisions to open discussion threads, surveys and consultation papers to all end users where possible. </li>
                      <li>There are a number of benefits to doing so:
                      <li>Our large internal audience comprising some 30,000 teachers and staff is a valuable and ready source to tap on for feedback on education policy initiatives and issues;</li>
                      <li>Keeping discussions, surveys and consultation papers open to all users will add energy and buzz to My Forum, which in turns encourages end users to actively engage Divisions in the surveys, consultation papers, and discussion forum; </li>
                      <li>The converse is true: if most of the activity is kept to specific interest groups, end users will not perceive My Forum to be an active platform for vibrant and dynamic interactions within the MOE Community. This will de-motivate users from further participation in My Forum;</li>
                      <li>Where a topic of discussion, survey or consultation paper appears to concern only a specific group of teachers and staff, views and comments from non-target groups of teachers and staff could provide fresh insight from a third-party&rsquo;s point of view. The third-party endorsement of an initiative or idea would also lend credibility to the results of an survey, consultation paper, or discussion.</li>
                      </li>
                              <li>Where Divisions decide to keep an survey or consultation paper &ldquo;private&rdquo;, Divisions may also consider publishing the results of the exercise for all end users in My Forum to view. Doing so signals to users that while they might not have been invited to &ldquo;private&rdquo; consultation paper exercises, MOE HQ is serious about closing the loop, and that we are open to letting our teachers and staff share in the findings of completed exercises</li>
                    </ol>                  </td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text">&nbsp;</td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td class="body_detail_text"><font size="4px" class="Table_Sub_Topic"><u><i>Selecting Participants for Targeted &ldquo;Private&rdquo; Consultation Papers and Surveys</i></u></font></td>
			      <td align="right" nowrap="nowrap">
							<a href="#top"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_up.gif' border="0" alt="Back"></a> <a href="#bottom"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_down.gif' border="0"></a></td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text"><ol>
				    <br>
                    <li>The My Forum Administration-User Profile module enables Division Administrators to select participants based on criteria such as Designation, Age Group, Level (i.e. Pri, Secondary, JC), Subject Teaching etc. MOE Staff that meet the criteria selected will be listed together with statistics on the number of consultation paper exercise they have participated in the past or are participating currently. </li>
				    <li>Division Administrators are encouraged to refer to these statistics and not tap on the same MOE staff unless absolutely necessary. This is to prevent survey/consultation paper exercise fatigue and ensure that a survey/consultation paper exercise will be given the appropriate attention.</li>
				    </ol>				  </td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text">&nbsp;</td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td class="body_detail_text"><font size="4px" class="Table_Sub_Topic"><u><i>Putting Up Consultation Papers for Feedback on My Forum</i></u></font></td>
			      <td  align="right" nowrap="nowrap">
							<a href="#top"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_up.gif' border="0" alt="Back"></a> <a href="#bottom"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_down.gif' border="0"></a></td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text"><br>
                    <ol>
                      <li>All Divisions will on their own, through their Division Administrator or Moderators, upload and format cleared consultation papers on My Forum.</li>
                      <li>Divisions are encouraged to close the loop upon the completion of the consultation paper exercise as mentioned in the &lsquo;Closing the Loop&rsquo; paper by CCD </li>
                    </ol>                  </td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text">&nbsp;</td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td class="body_detail_text"><font size="4px" class="Table_Sub_Topic"><u><i>Administering Surveys on My Forum</i></u></font></td>
			      <td  align="right" nowrap="nowrap">
							<a href="#top"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_up.gif' border="0" alt="Back"></a> <a href="#bottom"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_down.gif' border="0"></a></td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text"><ol><br>
                    <li>The My Forum survey module caters to surveys whose target audience comprises teachers and staff of a minimum of two schools and above. For local school surveys, Divisions are greatly encouraged to use the School Cockpit survey module. </li>
				    <li>All Division Administrators can format their surveys online using My Forum. Divisions would have to clear the survey with their respective Directors prior the administration of the survey.</li>
				    <li>Divisions are encouraged to close the loop upon the completion of the survey as mentioned in the &lsquo;Closing the Loop&rsquo; paper by CCD. </li>
				    </ol>				  </td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text">&nbsp;</td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td class="body_detail_text"><font size="4px" class="Table_Sub_Topic"><u><i>Administering Polls</i></u></font></td>
			      <td  align="right" nowrap="nowrap">
							<a href="#top"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_up.gif' border="0" alt="Back"></a> <a href="#bottom"><img src='<bean:message key="OIFM.docroot" />/images/Icons/icon_jump_down.gif' border="0"></a></td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
				  <td colspan="2" class="body_detail_text"><ol>
				    <br>
                    <li>The fortnightly poll will be administered by the Main Administrator. </li>
				    <li>All Divisions, upon clearance of their polls, will have to submit the poll to the Main Administrator for publishing on the My Forum, at least one month in advance. </li>
				    </ol>				  </td>
			  </tr>
				<tr>
